data.title: Great Mexican cuisine, fast
data.text: Generous portions of genuine home made style Mexican Food, for a great price. Good selection of standard fare along with specialty items not normally found at restaurants that emphasize 'food' fast.

data.title: Service was very fast, and the plate had a generous serving
data.text: We wanted a place just off the freeway and which would allow us access back onto the freeway.  This place gave us the answer.  We felt as if we wanted Mexican food, but not at one of the standard locations, and this place seemed as if a "local" person would run it.  We felt that the food was more home-made than other places, and we enjoyed it.

data.title: Food was BOMB, Open Late, Good Prices, Friendly Service
data.text:
We came here after a concert in San Bernadino at around 1 in the morning.
I was so happy to see: They have their entire menu available and the Drive Through is open 24/7.
The food was really good and the prices were very reasonable.
Hunny got the carne asada fries, and I got the cheese enchiladas combo plate.
SUPER yummy!

data.title: Delicious!
data.text: After waiting at the drive thru at the McDonalds for like 30 minutes for my son's food, I saw across the street just a little drive thru with an OPEN sign. Since it was so late, nothing was open except McDonalds and Steak n Shake and I did not want that.  This was a little Mexican drive thru open 24 hours, they have inside seating during the day.  The drive thru did have cars and filled up quickly so to me that is a good sign.  It took awhile  but t.he lady in front of me ordered a couple bags.  I figured this was being made from scratch which it was.  There were so many choices but I picked the 2 beef burrito combo plate with rice and beans.  The burritos had actual hunks of beef.  It was not ground beef. Also had peppers, jalepenos, tomato and both were giant. The carry out box was so heavy! Hot and delicious would definately repeat visit if I lived or was in this area. Plate was $7. 00 and could have fed more than 1 person if I wasnt so hungry.  This restaurant is off Mariposa

data.title: Surprisingly delicious
data.text: We stopped at this place by recommendation on-line and felt apprehension because it looks like a fast food restaurant, but everything was delicious. The portions are huge, the chips and guacamole were great. Watch out, all the salsas are really spicy. Very authentic place.
